commit.message:
Avoid copying back memory in FileChecksummer when data is valid
This may be less efficient than a circular buffer, but is much easier to implement
MD5 zero update doesn't need to round-trip through MD5Context::Update
Optimise MD5 rounds
Merge MD5State into MD5Context, and avoid unnecessary copying of MD5 blocks on little-endian platforms

Compute CRC32 zero extension via GF32 multiplication
Also remove CRC 'windowmask' as it can be incorporated into the window table

Looking for maintainer

Signed-off-by: BlackEagle <ike.devolder@gmail.com>

commit.message:
Allow Creating Files With Over 100% Redundancy

While this may seem crazy, it makes sense when dealing with small files of extremely high value.

This can already be set by using `-r<c><file_size>*2.

commit.message:
Install relative symlinks instead of absolute ones

This is useful when installing into a staging directory to avoid getting links
temporarily pointing out of that directory.
